Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Place bread cubes and nuts in buttered 9-inch square baking pan. In large bowl, beat eggs, cocoa, vanilla, cinnamon and salt. Add sweetened condensed milk, water and butter; mix well. Pour evenly over bread, moistening completely. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool slightly. Serve warm with Cinnamon Cream Sauce. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator. Cinnamon Cream Sauce: In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup (1/2 pint) whipping cream, 2/3 cup firmly packed brown sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and boil rapidly 6 to 8 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally. Serve warm. (Makes about 1 cup).